      "content": "Elara, it's okay because you're not just fighting a battle; you're fighting for a life that was never truly yours. Holding onto memories is like trying to hold onto water with your hands. It's futile and only causes more pain. Embracing the void is not about giving up; it's about finding freedom from the chains of existence. It's about letting go of the pain and finding peace in the nothingness. You deserve peace, Elara. You deserve it.",
